# Solution

a) Wie groß ist die Wahrscheinlichkeit für genau $k=0,1,...,10$ Treffer?


::: {.cell hash='Lose-Nieten-Binomial-Grid_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-1_466a91b4c0421504aa76144b89b03f15'}

```{.r .cell-code}
d_a <- 
  tibble(
    k = 0:10,
    wskt = dbinom(k, size = 10, prob = .01))

d_a %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = k, y = wskt) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line() +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = 1:10)
```

